cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with parsing and semantic interpretation of speech-based user interfaces. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of logical operators and a model of the application environment to resolve ambiguity. 
3. cs.LG (Learning) is a possible category as the paper may involve machine learning techniques for parsing and semantic interpretation. 
4. cs.SD (Sound) is a possible category as the paper deals with speech-based user interfaces. 
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of a speech-based user interface and its interaction with the application environment.
